review_blob: Really good entry by sam adams into the nitro realm. Best of the three nitros, should offer a mixed 4 pack. Holds up to murphys dry irish stout
Latest chance to try this was at Stub and Herbs on Darkness Eve. 2013 version. Awesome complexity here.
beer_name: Lift Bridge Silhouette Bourbon Barrel Aged Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Had this on BA version tap a few times before I actually cracked a bottle. Subdued on the bourbon barrel aspects, but this is still the good ole Darkness that weve all grown to love.
Had on tap at Toppling Goliath on the bottle release day. Perfect balance between coffee maple malt and alcohol. Top notch
12 ounce pour at the Chipotle Cultivate festival in Minneapolis for $6. Nutty finish - good complex porter.
On tap at the Decorah tap room. Aromas are great and in your face. Palate is what youre looking for in a DIPA
Bottle pour sample from a poker night. Thick and rich, awesome appearance and complexity.
beer_name: Toppling Goliath SR-71 Blackbird (2015 Bottling / Draft)

review_blob: Growler pour. Fairly balanced for the style between the malt and hops. Aroma missing a bit, maybe more aggressive dry hopping? Finish is clean with tastes of citrus as noted by brewer.
Solid gose for the summer time here from Boulevard. Wheat comes through more in this version than other brewerys.

$15 bomber poured into some champagne flutes per Schells on label suggestion. Appearance is awesome - nice and opaque cloudy peachy orange. Heavy sediment in the bottle bottom. Lively foam on the pour. Aromas of peach and wheat sourness. Taste is more tart than peach, but the peach is there on the back end for a great finish. Bubbly and delicious. My favorite of the Noble Star series to date.
Pint at the tap room. Biscuity and crisp. Good for the style. I think this could be right up a number of peoples alley. Summer time style, but Ill stick with the Traitor.
Put this bottle down during a Belgian tasting. Tripel flavors abound here with the fruit and burn.
Finally got around to trying one of these last Christmas - solid dubbel, but Ill just spring for the Abt 12 instead.
Just an OK dopplebock for me on this beer. Drank out of a pint glass from a bottle pour.
Had this one last summer from a can out in the sun. Decent stonger lager here.
Had this one as a sample at the MN State Fair Beer Exhibit. One of my favorites for this series so far from Schells
beer_name: Schell Noble Star  #4 - Black Forest Sour Cherry Weisse

review_blob: Picked up a six pack of these beers. First lager thats been barrel aged for me. Thin but still good for the style I guess.
beer_name: Schell Stag Series #9 - Cave Aged Barrel Aged Lager

review_blob: Tried this at Where the Wild Beers Are 2014 - another solid entry in this lineup for Schells
beer_name: Schell Noble Star  #6 - Dawn of Aurora

review_blob: Really good go to can for sours - keeps the price more reasonable too for the style. Good bite, salt and citrus.
beer_name: Destihl Wild Sour Series: Here Gose Nothin

review_blob: At this $13/sixer price point - this is the best in my book for a summer beer. grapefruit is the perfect pairing here.
Bottle from Zipps. Awesome IPA from this brewery. First Ive tried of any of their beers. Great aromas and bitter balance.
I really love this beer. On tap at various places (most recently the Surly Taproom). The hop profile is right up my alley, awesome aroma, very drinkable for the alcohol content.
beer_name: Surly / Amager Todd - The Axe Man (Surly Version)

review_blob: very good cider. $14.99 price tag for me. a good one to split with me wife as she likes the bubbly oaky spicy apple here.
On tap in Madison. Didnt hear about this brewery until I saw it started selling out at local stores. Solid IPA with great balance and nice aromas from the hops used.

Tried a pint of this at the new taproom down in Shakopee. High amount of hop aromas (citrus) and bitterness for the session style, which I like. Color is golden with moderate amount of foam with lower retention. Getting a bit of chemical taste on the palate in the finish - but otherwise a good beer to grab a couple of after work.
On tap at the new brewery tap room. Good hop aromas with some biscuit on the finish

Very good hefe representation. Strong banana, cloudy appearance and clean palate and finish. This was from a growler and can hang with some of the good German hefes. My favorite of the first 4 beers from this new brewery out in the boonies.

Growler over the holidays. Great aromas of roasty coffee like darkness. Nice foam that is retained. Taste is a dry stout for sure. A slight off putting after taste, but not enough to knock this beers quality overall. Good early effort from this brewery.
beer_name: Take 16 Stormy Jack Irish Dry Stout

review_blob: On tap at the state fair. Cloudy golden color with some good tartness for the typical IPA style. Good and different summer beer.
Growler shared with a bud while eating some pizza. Awesome aromas in the west coast style with grapefruit being strong. Taste is well balanced
On tap at the Town Hall Tap during their anniversary week. Awesome sweet stout with in your face coconut
Bottle poured into the IPA glass. Good aromas of dank and citrus. Taste is the right amount of bitter with some malt body
beer_name: Steel Toe Sticker Fight Double IPA

review_blob: split this bottle while watching the Vikes in Dec. 2014. Better when it warmed a bit. Strange brew, but I kinda like the peat vs. sour interplay
beer_name: Brau Brothers Bancreagie 26 Peated Sour Ale

review_blob: interesting take on this lager hybrid. good but my least favorite from the initial lineup tried at the brewery
beer_name: Bauhaus Brew Labs Wagon Party West Cast Lager

review_blob: my favorite of the initial offerings from this brewery. tried on tap from the source. good roast and color.
Solid pilsner here tried at the brewery during their first month. clean with a good amount of hops
beer_name: Bauhaus Brew Labs Wonderstuff Ne Bohemian Pilsner

review_blob: Split a bottle with my brother in law. Awesome aromas of cacao and rum. smooth with some chili on the finish
Small pour from a generous soul at Darkness Day 2014 that cracked a bottle. Very sweet and hard to detect much vanilla. Glad I tried it, but there are other whales Id rather chase next time.
beer_name: Three Floyds Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout (Bourbon Vanilla Bean)

review_blob: Bottle from a Tesco in Portsmouth. Decent enough ale that didnt stand out too much, but was enjoyable
Cask at a pub in Portsmouth - foam linger for a long time and was creamy. Good ale with my "steak"
Cask at Beefeater in Portsmouth - too light of a beer for my tastes, but has good roasted complexity
8 ounces on tap in Savage, MN. Surlys best anniversary beer since Five. Cloudy darker golden brown. Bitterness of note for the style. Good aromas of subtle whiskey. Sneaky strength.
Fairly light for a pumpkin beer but this is good enough for the style. Some weird aftertastes
Bottle poured into a big ol stein. The best Oktoberfest beer Ive had since New Glarus Staghorn
Best of the 12 pack. I like that they shot for higher gravity as opposed to a 5% option. Roasty and milky
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Ninkasi Beer Camp Double Latte

review_blob: Picked up a bottle in a mix six in WI. Average beer - light on complexity and nothing noteworthy to remember after finishing the bottle.
beer_name: Central Waters Slinte Scottish Style Ale

review_blob: Got a couple bottles from Belgium in a box. 2013 drank in 2014. Cherry was good with the sour.
Snagged a bottle of this from across the border in WI. Spendy! $42 damn! Awesome beer though, subtle on the booze and tastes like a less strong BCBS.
beer_name: AleSmith Speedway Stout - Bourbon Barrel Aged

review_blob: Chugged a can of this at a Guardians of the Galaxy premier. Awesome gose, light on the salt, strong on the sour/tart. I love that this is in a can - Id drink this often if it was easier to get in MN

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Bottle I picked up from France 44 to try this ageless classic out. Some day Im going to try and partially freeze a doppelbock and see if I can get this. Good strength and complexity
